content.text: Welcome to the first unofficial Secure Scuttlebutt Monero Pub! May you meet many interesting characters, and perform truly heroic tasks.
Test post. Making sure all the pipes are working.
`Created repo: ssb://%RA9OAMCfiQ6nN0NcURQgTcs/aRIwMZNt8HgFRsVEE5A=.sha256 (monero)`
It turns out the Monero git repo is a little bigger than git-ssb can digest at the moment...
`Created repo: ssb:\/\/%ZMp8ym3WbOezK77XPsK\/8ld\/+p1FxImPeqdQFfjR154=.sha256 (gitian.sigs) Let us try some of the smaller but still frequently-used repos
`Created repo: ssb:\/\/%M\/4oEtNSm9RKefaZoOKPwOH1jlCgKCWB5k9sb1m8nqQ=.sha256 (monero-site) `
We would like to say w00tw00t to our friends at blackhats.romanian.anti-sec . ZmEu be upon you in this new year.
There were 757 failed login attempts since the last successful login. Hello everybody, why not come in through the front door? There *is* an invite, you know...
[Welcome, Redditors\!](https://www.reddit.com/r/MoneroCommunity/comments/kokbll/monero_secure_scuttlebutt_pub_a_decentralized/)

Monero repos are imported [here](http://xmrpubwfjsix74fjjijvp5eblwzmihcbi4whkpaopgc7yuhsmlrtirid.onion:8080/%405hTpvduvbDyMLN2IdzDKa7nx7PSem9co3RsOmZoyyCM%3D.ed25519). Thanks @cel-desktop and the rest of the SSB community for the help\!
Which is more important? (a) Regularly syncing with github repo (b) Import main monero repo (c) Set up ssb_room chat room ?
Recent attacks on Tor had an affect on our Pub. Jiggled some wires and the data started flowing. Hopefully we are back in business now!
XMR Pub has now transitioned fully to clearnet at https://xmr-pub.net   This was done mostly to minimize barriers to entry, and due to curren attacks on Tor consensus
/r/Monero has nearly 200,000 subscribers! w00ttail -f ssb-server.log
... well, that is that happens when you forget to escape exclamation points, and your last command was looking at the log, LOL
/r/Monero has now [passed the 200,000 subscribers mark](https://www.reddit.com/r/Monero/comments/lq3lac/200k_subscribers_to_rmonero/)

And averaging [~25,000 transactions per day](https://bitinfocharts.com/comparison/monero-transactions.html) (about 8% of [BTC txn volume](https://bitinfocharts.com/comparison/bitcoin-transactions.html))
Monero Policy workgroup responses to regulatory bodies worldwide: https://moneropolicy.org

Work is underway to increase the Monero ring size by [an order of magnitude](https://github.com/moneromooo-monero/bitmonero/commit/20873b6ade3d5418518dd67678b5831445bae130#diff-2dab379d6b644bece542722ed23e2ebaa6977a22ddfd93233dc1621c713e3591R209). Repressive governments, surveillance corporations, and good old fashioned crooks are going to have to work all that much harder. #sorrynotsorry
\![xmr-sticker-big.jpg](&syx6WqWjLrL/bRvocHlo3JTEFLBugdhS4lYlEWN7G0Y=.sha256)
[xmr-sticker-big.jpg](&syx6WqWjLrL/bRvocHlo3JTEFLBugdhS4lYlEWN7G0Y=.sha256)
XMR<->BTC trustless atomic swaps now live on testnet: [revuo-monero issue 96](https://revuo-monero.com/issue-96.html)
Easily add Monero payments to your website: [monerointegrations.com](https://monerointegrations.com/)
DIY sources: https://github.com/monero-integrations/monero-integrations.github.io
Excellent video introduction to Monero and its technical, regulatory, and monetary strengths: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O58STfvxZnY
Your regular dose of Monero tips, news and memes: https://medium.com/themoneromoon

JUST RELEASED -- [anonymous DEX Haveno](https://github.com/haveno-dex/haveno/blob/master/README.md) (Esperanto for Harbor). Forked from Bisq, but using Monero as the base coin. Fully decentralized P2P, runs under Tor, all transactions fast and inexpensive on the Monero blockchain.
How Monero<->BTC atomic swaps work:[step-by-step](https://www.monerooutreach.org/stories/monero-atomic-swaps.html)
